Looks like I dont really fall into any of the categories so far hehe. I'm a 53 wizard, unguilded. My friends and I form a regular group, and most times we group in dungeons or somewhere similar. I have spent some time soloing, but only sometimes, the vast majority of my xp has come in grouping and dungeoning. If I had a choice between the 2, I would choose the epic.<br>
<br>
Why?<br>
<br>
Whenever I step foot into a dungeon, Manaskin comes up, if its not already. I value every hp of that rune. If I had the epic, all the better, more hp and protection from nukes as well. The Al'Kabor staff is a fantastic item, no doubt, fantastic mana regen. But I can get by on clarity. Sure it may mean we would have less downtime for me if I had the staff, but the downtime would still exist as we sit and wait for cleric mana to regen. When I think of the Al'Kabor staff I think &quot;gee thatd be nice&quot;, but when I think of the epic, I'm thinking &quot;damn I wish I had that!&quot;<br>
<br>
So I voted for SotF<br>
<br>
